---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Learn">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Learn</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink">
      Tutorials are being written alongside the product, in public — one technical topic a week
      (browser printing limitations, ESC/POS basics, local servers, printer detection, and more).
      Nothing published here yet.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink">
      In the meantime, <a href="https://github.com/portixhq/escpos-cheatsheet" class="text-accent hover:underline">escpos-cheatsheet</a>
      and <a href="/examples" class="text-accent hover:underline">/examples</a> cover the same
      ground in reference form.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-muted">Follow <a href="/changelog" class="hover:text-ink">/changelog</a> for what's shipping.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
